detaileddescription.para: This attribute represents the queue's internal hardware PFC continuous deadlock state. It is an aggregation of all HW state used to determine if a queue is in PFC deadlock based on state cached/maintained by the SDK. Consecutive queries of this attribute provide the PFC state for the queue for the interval period between the queries.
This attribute should only be queried as part of the PFC deadlock and recovery detection processing.
